race.comment: ESPECIAL KAI (4) has a strong overall record having five wins and six places from 15 starts including a last start success (25.36) over 450m at Ballarat. Rarely misses off this draw. Has the ability and looks a key chance this line-up. TANNER BALE (6) trailed the lead and fought on well to be beaten 3.5 lengths into second (30.29) at The Meadows in a Grade 5 over 525m. Goes well out of this box with a win and six minor placings. Expecting another good run. PAW REX (1) comes off an average run last start when eighth at this track over 435m behind Dr. Buck (25.30) in a Grade 5 H. Great chance to atone. JOLLY OLD MAC (2) will be hard to beat with a drop in distance.
